comments: She comes off a little cold at first but she\'s actually really nice. She has a lot of passion for teaching future educators. No tests in her class but quite a few papers. comments: Dr. Ketter is an AWESOME teacher. I have had her for several classes both lower division and now upper division. I believe she is one of my easiest classes. Yes, she asks for a lot and you have quite a few assignments but she lays them out for you and tells your EXACTLY what to do and what is expected in the class. I think she is a GREAT teacher!

comments: In the classroom, she treats you like you are 3 grade students. This is kind of helpful for teaching techniques, but when she grades its your work she is extremely tough. She does give a lot of feedback though. If you take her for lower division (easy)and then take her for upper division (insanely hard) you will see 2 completely different people.
